metadata.name: Train Station
metadata.description:
The city of Bauru developed from this train station. It was a great railway junction for lines that carried cargo and people in the State of São Paulo, contributing to the economic growth and strengthening of the State.

The building now belongs to the City Hall of Bauru and, despite its historical importance, is completely abandoned and destroyed.
